      <hedline>
        <hl1>Package Deal</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Fred Kanter letter comments on Rob Walker's April 1 column about tool for opening clamshell packaging</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I seem to recall that Russell Baker complained some years ago about the difficulty of opening a clamshell package (Consumed, Rob Walker. April 1). Baker's frustration led him to a hardware store, where he purchased a pair of pliers, contained of course in a clamshell package. His solution was to throw the packaged pliers under the wheels of a bus and return to his apartment to attack the other offending item.</p>
      </block>
